# =============================================================================
# Trivy Security Scan — Accepted Vulnerabilities
# =============================================================================
# These CVEs are known and accepted risks. Each has been evaluated and
# documented with a justification for why it is not immediately fixable.
#
# Review this file periodically and remove entries when fixes are available.
#
# Last reviewed: 2026-03-10

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Go stdlib — shipped in esbuild binary (vite devDependency) and nginx/Alpine
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Context: Security scan builds --target development which includes all
# devDependencies (vite, esbuild, vue-tsc, etc.). The Go CVEs come from the
# statically-linked Go runtime inside the esbuild binary AND from the Alpine
# base image Go components. These are build tools only — the production image
# (nginx:alpine serving static files) does not contain esbuild.
# Impact: NONE on production. esbuild is a JS bundler that processes trusted
# local source files during build. No network exposure, no user input parsing.
# Fix: awaiting esbuild release with Go >= 1.24.13 or 1.25.7, and Alpine
# base image update.
# Added: 2026-02-24
CVE-2025-68121  # crypto/tls: Unexpected session resumption (CRITICAL)
CVE-2025-58183  # archive/tar: Unbounded allocation parsing GNU sparse map (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61726  # net/url: Memory exhaustion in query parameter parsing (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61728  # archive/zip: Excessive CPU building archive index (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61729  # crypto/x509: DoS via crafted certificate (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61730  # crypto/tls: TLS 1.3 handshake multiple messages issue (HIGH)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# esbuild — build tool binary (vite devDependency)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Context: esbuild 0.25.12 is a transitive devDependency of vite 6.4.1.
# It is a JavaScript bundler used only during build, not at runtime.
# The CVE is in the esbuild binary itself, not in application code.
# Impact: NONE on production. Build-time only tool processing trusted sources.
# Fix: awaiting patched esbuild release.
# Added: 2026-02-24
CVE-2026-25639  # esbuild: vulnerability in build tool binary (HIGH)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# minimatch — transitive devDependency (vue-tsc, @vue/test-utils)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Context: minimatch 9.0.1/9.0.5 is pulled in transitively by:
#   - vue-tsc 2.2.12 -> @vue/language-core -> minimatch
#   - @vue/test-utils 2.4.6 -> js-beautify -> editorconfig -> minimatch
#   - @vue/test-utils 2.4.6 -> js-beautify -> glob -> minimatch
# All are devDependencies used only during type-checking and testing.
# npm audit fix --force would install vue-tsc@3.2.5 (breaking change).
# Impact: NONE on production. Pattern matching ReDoS requires crafted input
# to minimatch — only used internally by build/test tooling on trusted globs.
# Fix: awaiting vue-tsc and @vue/test-utils releases with minimatch >= 10.2.1.
# Added: 2026-02-24
CVE-2026-26996  # minimatch: ReDoS via repeated wildcards (HIGH)
# Added: 2026-03-05 — New minimatch CVEs (same context as CVE-2026-26996)
CVE-2026-27903  # minimatch: DoS due to unbounded (devDep, build-time only)
CVE-2026-27904  # minimatch: DoS via catastrophic backtracking (devDep, build-time only)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# rollup — transitive devDependency (vite)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Context: rollup 4.53.3 is a transitive devDependency of vite. Build tool only.
# Impact: NONE on production. Path traversal requires crafted input during build.
# Fix: awaiting vite/rollup upstream update to 4.59.0.
# Added: 2026-03-05
CVE-2026-27606  # rollup: RCE via Path Traversal (devDep, build-time only)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# tar — transitive dependency (if present in node_modules)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Context: tar 6.2.1 may appear as a transitive dependency in the development
# image's node_modules. It is NOT a direct or runtime dependency of the
# application. These are path traversal CVEs requiring crafted tar archives.
# Impact: NONE on production. No tar archive processing in the application.
# Fix: awaiting upstream packages to update to tar >= 7.5.8.
# Added: 2026-02-24
CVE-2026-23745  # tar: path traversal (HIGH)
CVE-2026-23950  # tar: path traversal (HIGH)
CVE-2026-24842  # tar: path traversal (HIGH)
CVE-2026-26960  # tar: path traversal (HIGH)
# Added: 2026-03-10 — New tar CVE (same context)
CVE-2026-29786  # tar: hardlink path traversal via drive-relative linkpath (HIGH)

